This documentation describes Solace Messaging for Pivotal Cloud Foundry (PCF). Solace Messaging for PCF is a multi-protocol message broker. The Solace Messaging for PCF tile registers a service broker on PCF and exposes its service plans on the Marketplace. Developers can provision Message VPNs on a Solace Virtual Message Router (VMR) by creating instances of the service plans using Apps Manager or the cf Command Line Interface (CLI).

## <a id='overview'></a>Overview

Solace Messaging for PCF enables developers to link their applications to a Solace VMR through a Message VPN. To learn more about these components, see the [Core Concepts](http://dev.solacesystems.com/docs/core-concepts/#message-router-concepts) topic in the Solace documentation.

Solace Messaging for PCF includes the following features:

* Support for a range of message exchange patterns, deployment environments, and qualities of service, including open APIs and protocols like JMS, MQTT and REST 
* Support for distributing data over long-distance WAN links and streaming between web applications, mobile devices and IoT devices like sensors and smart vehicles
* Guaranteed messaging
* Pub/sub and request/reply messaging
* Persistent message queues
* Maximum guaranteed message size of 10MB
* Up to 10KB topic subscriptions per queue
* Up to 1000 incoming connections
* Up to 1000 concurrent transacted sessions
* Up to 1MB in-flight concurrent messages

For examples of how PCF developers can configure their applications to use the Solace Messaging service, see the sample applications [GitHub repository](https://github.com/SolaceSamples/solace-samples-cloudfoundry-java).

