## <a id='prereqs'></a>Prerequisites

Solace Messaging for PCF has the following prerequisites:

* You must install the MySQL for PCF tile. When configuring the tile, set the maximum storage in the **Service Plan** section to 100 MB. See the MySQL for PCF [documentation](../p-mysql/) for more information on how to install and configure the tile.
* You must set up external Solace VMRs. See the [Get Started](http://dev.solacesystems.com/get-started/) guide in the Solace documentation for more information. The environment where you deploy your Solace VMRs must allow inbound connections on the following ports:
    * Port 22 to access the VMR shell
    * Port 8080 to access the VMR's Solace Elements Management Protocol (SEMP) configuration interface
    * Ports 7000 to 7035 to access the VMR's messaging services (you can modify this range when [configuring](installing.html) the tile)
* If your deployment filters outbound traffic, you must allow outbound traffic from your deployment to the Solace VMRs. 

## <a id='limitations'></a> Beta Limitations

The beta version of Solace Messaging for PCF currently does not include the following features:

* High availability
* TLS connections
* Client certificate-based authentication
* LDAP and RADIUS-based authentication

<p class="note"><strong>Note</strong>: Upgrading the tile will delete all  service instances and application bindings related to Solace Messaging for PCF.</p>

